==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: magenta
<hw>ma*gen"ta</hw> <pr>(m⟦adot⟧*j⟦ecr⟧n"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An aniline dye obtained as an amorphous
substance having a green bronze surface color, which dissolves to a
shade of red; also, the color; -- so called from <etsep>Magenta</etsep>,
in Italy, in allusion to the battle fought there about the time the dye
was discovered. Called also <altname>fuchsin</altname>,
<altname>fuchsine</altname>, <altname>roseine</altname>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The purplish-red color of magenta.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magged</ent>⟦br⟧
